<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-01-19T21:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-01-19T21:00:00-05:00" n="374" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d374">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">701.9491/16: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Iran</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Dreyfus</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-01-19T21:00:00-05:00">January
                                    19, 1942—9 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>13. Your no. 8, January 13, 4 p.m. You may inquire informally of the
                            Prime Minister<note n="80" xml:id="d374fn80">Mohammed Ali
                                Foroughi.</note> as to the intentions of the Iranian Government
                            regarding the maintenance or severance of diplomatic relations with
                            Japan.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>